## Key Patterns

### Vault (Key Storage)
```typescript
// Load
const vault = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("launchpad-vault") || "{}");
// Save
localStorage.setItem("launchpad-vault", JSON.stringify(vault));
// Check connection
const isConnected = (svc: string) => {
  if (svc === "supabase") return !!(vault.supabase_url && vault.supabase_anon);
  return !!vault[svc];
};
```

### Agent Memory (Persistent)
```typescript
// Memories persist in localStorage, grouped by project
// Key: "launchpad-agent-memories"
// Format: Array of { id, project, content, type, created, task }
// Injected into Claude system prompt on each agent task
```

### API Call Pattern
```typescript
// All service APIs follow same pattern:
const ghFetch = async (endpoint: string, options = {}) => {
  const res = await fetch(`https://api.github.com${endpoint}`, {
    ...options,
    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${vault.github}`, ...options.headers },
  });
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(/* parse error */);
  return res.json();
};
```

### Toast Notifications
```typescript
showToast("Message here", "success"); // success | error | info | warning
```

## What's Working

All four integrations are wired to real APIs:
- GitHub: repos, branches, PRs, create/delete repos
- Vercel: projects, deployments, env vars (CRUD), project domains, deploy trigger
- Domains panel: TLD search (Vercel status API), registrar links, connect domain to project, account domain list
- Supabase: tables, data browser, SQL console, storage buckets
- Claude: live chat (Messages API), model selector, prompt vault, usage tracking
- Agent Bay: task launcher with memory layer, sessions audit
- MCP Config Generator: Claude Code + Cursor formats
- Dashboard: real-time health, cost cockpit, alerts
- Settings: vault with show/hide, add/remove keys
- Marketing: `/` landing + `/pricing`; Clerk sign-in/up; dashboard at `/app` (middleware-gated when Clerk env is set)

## What's Coming Next (Don't Build Yet)

- Stripe + Clerk Billing enforcement (Pro gate in `/app`)
- Migrate localStorage vault to Supabase Vault (Phase B)
- PWA / mobile (Phase E)

## Code Style

- Functional components with hooks only. No class components.
- Inline styles for dynamic values (service-specific colors). Tailwind for layout/spacing.
- Animations: use CSS keyframes defined in globals.css, not JS animation libraries.
- Keep toast notifications for all user-facing actions.
- Every panel has three states: disconnected (show connect CTA), loading (spinner), connected (show data).
- Error states always offer Retry + Update Token options.

## Important Context

- The plan.md in the project root has the full roadmap, business model, and launch plan.
- This app was prototyped in a Claude chat session and is being migrated to a real Next.js project.
- The founder is an ops guy, not a developer. Keep things simple, avoid unnecessary abstractions, and prefer working code over perfect architecture.
- Target launch: 4 weeks from now on ProductHunt.
- Pricing: Free (1 project, read-only) + Pro ($9.99/mo, everything).
